2026-04-20 11:55:24 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Relay contacts in control module'] hypothesis_explanation='The relay contacts inside the control module are showing a large voltage drop, with only about 0.36 V at the negative terminal when measured across the closed relay, despite the input being a solid 12 V. This is highly indicative of relay contact degradation or high contact resistance, which can intermittently drop the output voltage below what is needed for the lamp. This matches the symptom of the lamp periodically turning off and on, even though the relay switching should be stable. Previous tests confirm the lamp periodic switching is not related to timing or sensitivity adjustments. The cable connections are not faulty, as shown by observation and previous replacement attempt. Thus, relay contacts themselves are the suspected faulty components.'
