description: Measure the output voltage signal from the light sensor circuit during the periods when the lamp turns off and on. This will reveal if momentary drops or spikes in sensor output are causing the relay to switch, leading to the lamp's periodic off cycle., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened. The measured voltage at the ambient light sensor is 0.119 V (p) and 0.0003 V (n), while the main bulb shows voltages of 0.0003 V (p) and 0.0003 V (n). No polarity inversion was detected in the measured cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay output terminals in control module,
description: Measure the voltage at the relay output terminals (the switched cable pair) during both lamp-on and lamp-off states. This will confirm whether the relay is opening and closing as expected, or if there's intermittent switching causing the lamp to turn off for half a second every 20 seconds., outcome='Voltage at the Control Relay positive terminal is 11.99\u202fV, while the Control Output Cable (+) reads 0.36\u202fV and the Control Output Cable (−) reads 0.0003\u202fV. This suggests there is a significant voltage drop between the relay output and the control output cables. No POLARITY INVERSION is detected based on cable labeling and measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module output cable terminals and connections,
description: Visually inspect the terminals and fast connectors joining the relay outputs to the control module output cables for signs of loose contact, corrosion, or damage that may cause intermittent connection and voltage drop., outcome='The inspection found no observable internal faults, loose contacts, corrosion, or damage on the Control Relay, Control Output Cable (+), or Control Output Cable (−). Both cables are connected, with their positive terminals hidden inside the Control Cube. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=35.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Relay contacts inside the control module,
description: Measure the voltage directly across the relay contacts inside the control module during lamp-on and lamp-off periods to check if the relay is experiencing contact bounce, intermittent switching, or degradation., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened, allowing access to the internal components. The voltage measured across the control relay shows 11.9873 V at the positive terminal and 0.3592 V at the negative terminal. No polarity inversion was detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Connection between control module and load module,
description: Test the voltage at the input terminals of the load module (just before the diode) during both lamp-on and lamp-off periods. This will determine if the voltage drop occurs at the interface between modules, indicating possible poor contact or internal fault in the load module input circuitry., outcome='The voltage measured at Load Input Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, and at Load Input Cable (−) is 0.0003 V. There is no indication of a polarity inversion at the input terminals of the load module based on these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module internal ground/0V line,
description: Test the voltage continuity and resistance across the internal ground (0V) line of the control module, from battery negative to load module input. This will check for high resistance or partial loss of connection on the negative return path, which could explain the persistent low voltage on positive terminals and intermittent lamp operation., outcome='The continuity test between PSU Output Cable (−) and Load Input Cable (−) shows a short with low resistance (0.3 Ω), indicating a continuous connection. No polarity inversion detected on this path.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
